    cito:cites <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262778> ;
    dc:creator "Chérot, F.; Malipatil, M. B." ;
    dc:title "Orientomiris Yasunaga 1997" ;
    trt:augmentsTaxonConcept <http://taxon-concept.plazi.org/id/Animalia/Orientomiris_Yasunaga_1997> ;
    trt:publishedIn <http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4126.2.1> ;
    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4126.2.1>
    bibo:endPage "206" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "151" ;
    bibo:volume "4126" ;
    dc:creator "Chérot, F.; Malipatil, M. B." ;
    dc:date "2016" ;
    dc:title "A review of Adelphocoris - Creontiades - Megacoelum complex (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae: Mirini), with descriptions of two new genera and four new species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262778> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.262778>
    dc:description "FIGURES 25 – 27. Dorsal punctations in ACMc. Most common combinations of character states: 25. Case of Adelphocorisella lespedezae Miyamoto & Yasunaga, 1993. Hemelytra with only one type of punctation, dense, the punctures narrow and shallow (A, B). 26. Case of Orientomiris tricolor (Scott, 1880). Hemelytra with two types of punctations, one very dense, the punctures narrow and shallow (A example at right of the square, detail in C), the second slightly wider, surrounding the base of setae (A example in the square, detail in B). 27. Case of Chimsunchartella schwartzi Chérot & Pauwels, 2000. Hemelytra with two types of punctations: one relatively dense, narrow and shallow (A, B), but difficult to see, partially hidden by the dorsal pilosity, the second sparse, wider (details in B, arrows). Scales = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/262778/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

